                                                                        <p>Hadith to report:</p>
                                                                        <p>4. From him, from Muhammad Bin Ali Al Hamdany, from Amro Bin Isa, from Furat Bin Ahnaf who said, ‘Abu Abdullah (a.s.) was asked about the leek?’ So he (a.s.) said: ‘Eat it, for therein are four qualities – It is good for the marriage, and expels the wind, and suppresses the haemorrhoids (piles), and it is a safety from the leprosy for the one who is habitual in (eating) it’.</p>
