                                                                        <p>5. From him, form a number of our companions, from Ibn Sinan, from Abu Al Jaroud, from Ziyad Bin Sowqat, from Al Husayn Bin Al Hassan, from his forefathers who said, ‘Amir Al-Momineen (a.s.) said to me: ‘I (a.s.) saw Rasool-Allah (saww), and I (a.s.) recognised the hunger in his (saww) face. So I (a.s.) drew ten buckets (of water from a well) for a woman of the Helpers, so I (a.s.) took from her (in return) dates and something from the leeks. So I (a.s.) made these to be in my (a.s.) lap, then I (a.s.) came to Rasool-Allah (saww) with these and fed him (saww)’.</p>
