                                                                        <p>Hadith to report:</p>
                                                                        <p>7. From him, from Ali Bin Hasaan, from Musa Bin Bakr who said, ‘A slave of Abu Al-Hassan (a.s.) had complained, so he (a.s.) asked about him. He (a.s.) was told that it was his spleen, so he (a.s.) said: ‘Feed him the leek for three days’. So we fed it to him. He bled for a day then was free (from it)’.</p>
