                                                                        <p>18. From him, from Ibrahim Bin Uqba Al Khazai’e, from Yahya Bin Suleyman who said, ‘I saw Abu Al-Hassan (a.s.) Al-Ridha (a.s.) at Khorasan in a garden and he (a.s.) was eating the leek. So I said to him (a.s.), ‘May I be sacrificed for you (a.s.)! The people are reporting that the endive, there falls upon it a drop from the Paradise every day’. So he (a.s.) said: ‘If there was a drop upon the endive, so the leek is immersed in the water in the Paradise’. I said, ‘So (what about) the fertiliser’. So he (saww) said: ‘Nothing can be associated with it’.</p>
